 and architect himself, James manages Lullabot's back-end development team. He lives near Atlanta, GA and enjoys fishing, hiking, and camping.","position":"Development Manager","expertise":["Continuous Integration","Automated Testing","Drupal","PHP"],"body":{"value":"\u003cp>Like many in the web development world, James came to programming through the side door. After graduating with a degree in music performance, he decided in 2004 to start a record label and began searching for tools to help him build websites for the bands he was working with. A recommendation from a fellow nerd landed him on the \u003ca href=\"https://www.drupal.org\">Drupal homepage\u003c/a>. Drupal 4.5 was the current release at the time, and while he got a lot for free from the community, he soon found that he had quite a bit to learn in order to be able to build the simple yet unique websites his musicians wanted.\u003c/p>\n\n\u003cp>Thankfully, James took to PHP and web development quickly. As his skills increased and interest grew, he began learning other technologies, and built one of the first \u003ca href=\"https://www.lullabot.com/podcasts/drupalizeme-podcast/decoupling-drupal\">decoupled Drupal\u003c/a> websites using a Drupal 5 backend that fed XML to a Flash frontend website. It wasn't long before James realized that he was receiving more compliments on the websites he was building than for the music, and so he hung up his record label hat and began to pursue a full time career in Drupal development.\u003c/p>\n\n\u003cp>Since then, it has been a continual growth journey for James. After working as the Drupal developer for Sprocket, a web design agency based in metro Atlanta, he was hired as a part-time Drupal trainer for Lullabot, then as a developer, senior developer, and then architect—all for some of the world's biggest brands. James has worked on large data migrations for \u003ca href=\"https://www.grammy.org\">The Recording Academy\u003c/a>, engaging editorial experiences for \u003ca href=\"http://www.msnbc.com\">MSNBC\u003c/a>, and helped create a fast and stable development and deployment process for \u003ca href=\"https://supportforums.cisco.com\">Cisco's Support Forum\u003c/a>. He architected a decoupled user experience for \u003ca href=\"http://www.marthastewart.com\">Martha Stewart\u003c/a>, and a continuous integration and deployment process for \u003ca href=\"https://www.intel.com\">Intel\u003c/a>, which later became \u003ca href=\"https://tugboat.qa\">Tugboat\u003c/a>.\u003c/p>\n\n\u003cp>As a development manager, James helps Lullabot hire the best Drupal developers in the world, empowering them to continue bringing \u003ca href=\"/values\">Lullabot's values\u003c/a> to everything they do, and matching their skills up with our client's needs, all while continuing to do development and architecture consulting himself. Though he does wear many hats, in real life he prefers to wear either bow ties or waders.\u003c/p>\n","format":"markdown"},"quote_text":"","quote_cite":"","fact":"","time_zone":"America/New_York","location":"Duluth, GA","promos":[],"links":{"drupalorg":"q0rban","dribbble":"","facebook":"","flickr":"","github":"q0rban","googlePlus":"","lanyrd":"","linkedIn":"","twitter":"q0rban"},"external":[],"image":{"fid":"3401","uri":"bios/headshot_james.jpg","mime":"image/jpeg","alt":"","caption":"","title":""},"hero_image":{"fid":"4435","uri":"mexico_james_alt.jpg","mime":"image/jpeg","alt":"Fly Fishing in Mexico","caption":"","title":""},"hero_image_invert":true,"map":{"fid":"3015","uri":"maps/map_james-opt.svg","mime":"image/svg+xml","alt":"","caption":"","title":"","contents":"\u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" version=\"1.1\" x=\"0px\" y=\"0px\" viewBox=\"0 0 50.8 33.1\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 50.8 33.1\" xml:space=\"preserve\">\u003cpath d=\"M50.8 4.1v1.5c0 0.4-0.1 0.9-0.4 1.2L46 13.1v0.1l0.4 4.4c0.1 0.5-0.1 1-0.4 1.4l-3.4 5.1 c0 0 0 0.1 0 0.2l2.1 5.3c0.3 0.7 0.2